    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (80.92) is our clear centerpiece, benefiting from a high base projection and a favorable matchup against Civale, who holds a soft 4.45 xERA. Following closely are **Taylor Ward** (64.43) and **Jonathan Aranda** (66.61). **Taylor Ward** is a high-upside play at the top of the order; despite the presence of a tough arm like Fried, **Taylor Ward** leverages a massive platoon advantage and favorable wind conditions to project well. **Jonathan Aranda** similarly exploits a soft matchup against Mahle, with his spot in the three-hole and positive xwOBA trends making him an essential component of our daily foundation.\n\nIn the middle infield, **Geraldo Perdomo** (60.42) remains a priority start, largely due to his spot in the two-hole and wind conditions that favor his profile against Boyd. Our most difficult decision on the bench was **Luis Arraez** (42.11), who narrowly missed the cut. While he offers a safe floor, his projected efficiency fell just short of **Matt Chapman** (43.27) and **Daulton Varsho** (51.21), as the latter two carry more robust dynamic platoon advantages in their respective matchups. We continue to monitor **Masyn Winn** (45.97) and **Wenceel Perez** (48.73), both of whom are pushed into the starting lineup due to their elite stolen base potential; in our 5x5 format, prioritizing speed against pitchers with slower deliveries is a calculated risk that outweighs marginal gains in batting average.\n\nRisks for today center on the tougher pitching matchups, specifically the pair of **Taylor Ward** and **Jeremiah Jackson** (44.94) facing Fried. While the wind provides a lift, the elite skill set of the opposing starter introduces volatility that could suppress counting stats. We are also keeping a close watch on **Jung Hoo Lee**, who fell below our 40.0 floor today and remains on the bench, alongside **Cal Raleigh**, **Lawrence Butler**, **Will Smith**, **Tyler Freeman**, **Yainer Diaz**, **Gleyber Torres**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Gavin Sheets**, and **Drew Gilbert**, all of whom are currently out of the rotation due to lack of lineup confirmation or rest. We proceed with the current configuration, banking on the speed-heavy profile of the starting nine to keep us competitive in the SB category while leveraging the platoon edges of **Jonathan Aranda** and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** for offensive production.",
